 Appearances (Goals). Filippo Maria Scardina (born 26 February 1992) is an Italian footballer who plays for F.C. Esperia Viareggio on loan from A.S. Roma. Scardina was call-up to Roma first team against PFC CSKA Sofia in the UEFA Europa League. He substituted Stefano Okaka Chuka in the 81st minute and scored a goal 8 minutes later.[1] The match ended in 3-0 won. Before the match Roma has ensured to advance to next stage and CSKA has been eliminated. 
